---
import Section from "~/components/Section.astro";
import Stage from "~/components/Stage.astro";
---

<Section id="problem" num="01" title="The problem">
  <p>
    A Bitcoin wallet wants to ask a server: <em>"Do I own any UTXOs under
    scripthash&nbsp;X?"</em>  A naive request writes X in the clear. The server
    — or anyone who can see the traffic — learns every address you care about.
  </p>
  <p>
    The only other option is to download the whole UTXO set yourself and check
    locally. That's &gt;&nbsp;10&nbsp;GB and growing, and it ships every
    ratchet of other people's addresses to your device just so you can check
    your own. <strong>Private Information Retrieval (PIR)</strong> sits
    between these two extremes: the server answers the question without ever
    learning which question you asked.
  </p>

  <Stage
    caption="Left: naive wallet leaks the scripthash. Right: PIR wallet sends an opaque query blob."
    label="Naive request versus PIR request"
  >
    <svg
      viewBox="0 0 680 260"
      role="img"
      aria-label="Diagram comparing a naive request (scripthash visible) with a PIR request (opaque blob)"
      data-anim="problem"
    >
      <defs>
        <marker id="arr-accent" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5"
          markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="currentColor"/>
        </marker>
      </defs>
      <!-- Left panel: naive -->
      <g transform="translate(0,0)">
        <text x="80" y="22" class="svg-label" fill="var(--danger)">NAIVE</text>
        <rect x="14" y="40" width="120" height="58" rx="8"
          class="svg-dim" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="74" y="66" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)"
          font-size="12" font-weight="600">Wallet</text>
        <text x="74" y="84" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">Alice</text>
        <rect x="196" y="40" width="120" height="58" rx="8"
          class="svg-dim" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="256" y="66" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)"
          font-size="12" font-weight="600">Server</text>
        <text x="256" y="84" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">UTXO DB</text>

        <path d="M 138 69 L 192 69" stroke="var(--danger)" stroke-width="1.5"
          fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr-accent)" color="var(--danger)"
          stroke-dasharray="5 4" class="pkt-path"/>
        <g class="pkt pkt-naive">
          <rect x="140" y="56" width="52" height="26" rx="5"
            fill="var(--danger)" opacity="0.18" stroke="var(--danger)"/>
          <text x="166" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--danger)">sh=76a9…ab</text>
        </g>
        <text x="166" y="120" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label"
          fill="var(--danger)">scripthash visible</text>

        <g transform="translate(0,150)" opacity="0.9">
          <text x="14" y="16" class="svg-label">Server learns:</text>
          <text x="14" y="34" font-size="12" fill="var(--fg)">→ Alice's address</text>
          <text x="14" y="52" font-size="12" fill="var(--fg)">→ her balance</text>
          <text x="14" y="70" font-size="12" fill="var(--fg)">→ her activity</text>
        </g>
      </g>

      <line x1="340" y1="20" x2="340" y2="240" stroke="var(--border)"
        stroke-dasharray="3 4"/>

      <!-- Right panel: PIR -->
      <g transform="translate(360,0)">
        <text x="80" y="22" class="svg-label" fill="var(--ok)">PIR</text>
        <rect x="14" y="40" width="120" height="58" rx="8"
          class="svg-dim" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="74" y="66" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)"
          font-size="12" font-weight="600">Wallet</text>
        <text x="74" y="84" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">Alice</text>
        <rect x="196" y="40" width="120" height="58" rx="8"
          class="svg-dim" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="256" y="66" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--fg)"
          font-size="12" font-weight="600">Server</text>
        <text x="256" y="84" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">UTXO DB</text>

        <path d="M 138 69 L 192 69" stroke="var(--ok)" stroke-width="1.5"
          fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr-accent)" color="var(--ok)"
          class="pkt-path"/>
        <g class="pkt pkt-pir">
          <rect x="140" y="56" width="52" height="26" rx="5"
            fill="var(--ok)" opacity="0.15" stroke="var(--ok)"/>
          <text x="166" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--ok)">██ ██ ██</text>
        </g>
        <text x="166" y="120" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label"
          fill="var(--ok)">opaque DPF / FHE blob</text>

        <g transform="translate(0,150)" opacity="0.9">
          <text x="14" y="16" class="svg-label">Server learns:</text>
          <text x="14" y="34" font-size="12" fill="var(--fg)">→ a query occurred</text>
          <text x="14" y="52" font-size="12" fill="var(--fg)">→ <em>nothing</em> about which row</text>
          <text x="14" y="70" font-size="12" fill="var(--fg)">→ <em>nothing</em> about Alice</text>
        </g>
      </g>
    </svg>
  </Stage>

  <p>
    <strong>What PIR guarantees:</strong> the server processes your query
    without learning which entry in the database you read. <strong>What it
    costs:</strong> the server must touch <em>every</em> row — privacy comes
    from making every query look identical. BitcoinPIR is about making that
    cost acceptable for real wallets on real devices.
  </p>
</Section>

<style>
  .pkt-naive, .pkt-pir { opacity: 0; transform-origin: 140px 69px; }
  [data-anim="problem"].play .pkt-naive {
    animation: slide 2.4s var(--ease) 0.2s both;
  }
  [data-anim="problem"].play .pkt-pir {
    animation: slide 2.4s var(--ease) 0.6s both;
  }
  @keyframes slide {
    0%   { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(0); }
    15%  { opacity: 1; }
    80%  { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(28px); }
    100% { opacity: 0.4; transform: translateX(28px); }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .pkt-naive, .pkt-pir { opacity: 1 !important; }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-anim="problem"]').forEach((svg) => {
    const stage = svg.closest("[data-stage]");
    const run = () => {
      svg.classList.remove("play");
      void svg.getBoundingClientRect();
      svg.classList.add("play");
    };
    stage?.addEventListener("stage:visible", run);
    svg.addEventListener("click", run);
  });
</script>
